A: You are using the same iterator in each loop iteration. You should create a new iterator for each loop iteration.
Here is the corrected code:
for (DataSnapshot dataSnapshot1:dataSnapshot.getChildren()) {
    i = i + 1;
    Iterator<DataSnapshot> it = dataSnapshot1.getChildren().iterator();
    while(it.hasNext()) {
        names.add(it.next().getValue(String.class));
    }
}

This will iterate over each child of the DataSnapshot and then iterate over each child of those children.

